==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|adjectif|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|adiectivus|adiectīvum|lang=la}}, from {{term|ad||next to|lang=la}} + {{term|iectus|-iect-|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|iacio|iaciō|throw|lang=la}} + {{term|-ivus|-īvus|lang=la}}, adjective ending; hence, a word "thrown next to" a noun, modifying it.

